.Dd $Mdocdate: May 9 2020 $
.Dt cnd_signal 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm cnd_signal
.Nd signal a condition.
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Lb threads
.In threads.h
.Ft int
.Fn cnd_signal "cnd_t *cnd"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The function
.Fn cnd_signal
will wake up exactly one thread waiting on the condition variable 
.Fa cnd
for it to reread the condition variable.
.Pp
The thread calling
.Fn cnd_signal
does not need to have acquired the condition variable signaled.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Upon success
.Fn cnd_signal
returns 
.Va thrd_success , 
otherwise 
.Va thrd_error
will be returned. 
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr cnd_init 3
.Xr cnd_destroy 3
.Xr cnd_broadcast 3
.Xr cnd_timedwait 3
.Xr cnd_wait 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn cnd_signal
function first appeared in the C11 standard ISO/IEC 9899:2011.
